      • move

        public void move(double x,
        double y,
        double rotation)
        Moves forward at magnitude x and left at magnitude y. Rotates clockwise with speed rotation. Negative values will result in reverse directions (reverse, right, and counterclockwise respectively).
        Parameters:
        x - The forward speed
        y - The left speed
        rotation - The rotation speed

      • moveDistance

        public boolean moveDistance(double distance,
                   double direction,
                   double speed)
        The moveDistance method uses polar coordinates to determine where to go and how fast to get there. The distance parameter is how far you want the robot to go. Call this in some sort of loop, it has no internal one.
        Parameters:
        distance - The distance to travel
        direction - The direction in degrees
        speed - The magnitude of the motors to travel at
        Returns:
        Whether or not the target distance was reached
